<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Cali:
[B]In terms of EQ when people say "Bot" or "Dual boxing" they mean they are running 2 characters on 2 machines at once. (Or more!)

While I highly recommend playing the cleric in groups without the monk, to learn HOW to be a good cleric, here are some hints that may help.

Helpful social keys to make a cleric a 2nd box are:

The Follow Key:
/target Monk
/follow

The Heal Key:
/target Monk
/sit off
/cast 1 (or whatever number the heal is)
/pause 20
/sit on


While I am NO MEANS an expert, I did a bit of 2boxing recently and found it MUCH easier to play the melee and only use the cleric hotkeys as needed.  With a horse and an outdoor zone, you dont ever need to /sit off so its a good thing.

Good luck.
[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
